{{Quote|You see? You ''must'' allow yourself your own private guards, Supreme Chancellor!|Senator Viento to Chancellor Palpatine|<ref name="Bloodlines" />}}
The '''Red Guard''', nicknamed '''Redrobes''', was an elite [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|organization]] of [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguards]] trained to protect [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], the [[Head of State (disambiguation)|head of state]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. Its first members were drawn from the ranks of the [[Senate Guard/Legends|Senate Guard]]. Guardsmen noted for loyalty and efficiency were transferred into the [[Red]] Guard; [[Senate Commando/Legends|Senate Commandos]]&mdash;regarded as the best and the bravest [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] of the Senate Guard&mdash;were also assimilated into the Chancellor's private security unit.

The Red Guard served as Chancellor Palpatine's protectors prior to and throughout the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy-wide]] [[civil war]] between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. After the Republic's [[Declaration of a New Order|transition]] into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] was completed by the end of the war in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], the Red Guard was reorganized into the [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Emperor's Royal Guard]] by the newly-appointed [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine.

==History==
{{Quote|Yes, I remember how powerful the Red Guards were. They used to bully us.|[[Kambrea]]|<ref name="Young Jedi Knights: Delusions of Grandeur">''[[Young Jedi Knights: Delusions of Grandeur]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Guard.png|thumb|left|150px|A Red Guard in full uniform]]
The formation of the [[Red]] Guard was initiated shortly after the [[Supreme Chancellor election, 32 BBY/Legends|election]] of [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]].<ref name="Bloodlines" /> For [[Standard century/Legends|centuries]], the [[Senate Guard/Legends|Senate Guard]], in addition to providing security to the [[Senator/Legends|elected officials]] of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]], served as the elite [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguards]] to the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Head of State (disambiguation)|head of state]].<ref name="EncyclopediaSG">{{SWE|groups|senateguard|Senate Guard}}</ref> Allegations of corruption undermined the Senate Guard's reputation, leading to calls for the creation of a separate unit for the Chancellor's protection.<ref name="Bloodlines" />

The Senate Guard's traditional role as the Supreme Chancellor's [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|security]] service detail was ultimately supplanted after several [[Assassin/Legends|assassins]] infiltrated its ranks in an apparent conspiracy to murder Palpatine. Though the plot was thwarted by the intervention of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Ronhar Kim]], Senator [[Viento]] saw the incident as a prime example as to why the Chancellor needed a unit that was independent from the Senate Guard and more closely monitored by the [[Office of the Supreme Chancellor/Legends|executive branch]]. The end result was establishment of the Red Guard,<ref name="Bloodlines" /> a group composed of [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] chosen from the old Guard's best and most loyal members. Even some of the elite [[Senate Commando/Legends|Senate Commandos]] were transferred into the ranks of the new unit.<ref name="GAW">''[[Galaxy at War]]''</ref>

Afterward, Chancellor Palpatine's further public appearances normally saw him flanked by a pair of Red Guards, especially during the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]].<ref name="RRMFundraiser">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|53|news/13425_4.html|RRM Fundraiser a Huge Success}}</ref> The sight of the Republic's leader and his private guards was interpreted as a sign of the heightened security within the Republic that was on the verge of a [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] [[civil war]].<ref name="LetsTalk">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|48|news/13321_1.html|Palpatine to Separatists: Let's Talk}}</ref> For example, when Palpatine presided over the [[Trial of Ahsoka Tano/Legends|trial]] of [[Ahsoka Tano/Legends|Ahsoka Tano]], members of the Red Guard were on the dais with him standing watch.<ref name="TWJ">{{TCW|The Wrong Jedi}}</ref> Despite the advocacy for the Red Guard's creation and the Chancellor's initial show of preference for maintaining the Senate Guard as his protectors,<ref name="Bloodlines" /> the Red Guard was regarded as a controversial topic.<ref name="LetsTalk" /> Some members of the Senate, believed that the Red Guards were [[Galactic Constitution/Legends|unconstitutional]], absent of a formal act or approval from the legislature. However, in large part because such accusations ran the risk of violating the new security laws established by Palpatine, any objections were very rarely voiced.<ref name="Visual Dictionary">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref><ref name="Complete Visual Dictionary">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

The Red Guard continued to exist in its capacity as the private security force of Chancellor Palpatine and acted as his emissaries throughout the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]],<ref name="EpisodeII" /><ref name="EpisodeIII" /> the conflict that resulted from the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] Rebellion against the Galactic Republic.<ref name="EpisodeII" /> Senate Commandos&mdash;including regular guardsmen&mdash;were still occasionally retained as the Chancellor's bodyguards during the war.<ref name="SW:TCW">[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars'' film]]</ref><ref name="Senate Murders">{{TCW|Senate Murders}}</ref> By the near end of the Clone Wars, the Red Guard's reputation was mixed between respect for the skills of its members, and mystery regarding the specific details of its organization. Although its members were acknowledged as highly-trained soldiers by [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], their full strength and numbers remained confidential to outsiders.<ref name="LOE">''[[Labyrinth of Evil]]''</ref> With the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] surrounding the Chancellor,<ref name="EpisodeIII" /> and the secretive nature of the Red Guard, the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] came to suspect that the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] had infiltrated the ranks of Palpatine's bodyguards.<ref name="LOE" />

[[File:JQFalsePeace.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Chancellor Palpatine and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], flanked by two Red Guards]]
During the [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|Battle of Coruscant]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], the Red Guard protected Chancellor Palpatine<ref name="LOE" /> alongside their [[blue]] Senate Guard counterparts, [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]], and even the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]].<ref name="Clone Wars 24">{{CW|24}}'</ref> They also aided in the defense of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant's]] [[Senate District/Legends|Senate District]] in [[Galactic City/Legends|Galactic City]] under the command of [[High Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]]. As the fighting wore on, some of the Guard's members even expressed anxiety over Palpatine's refusal to retreat to a safer location.<ref name="LOE" />

Following the Republic victory on Coruscant, Chancellor Palpatine revealed himself to the Jedi as [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious, the enigmatic [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] who eluded the Council's attempts to discover him throughout the Clone Wars. He used his various [[Emergency Powers Act/Legends|emergency powers]] and the [[Inhibitor chip/Legends|programmed loyalty]] of the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Clone Army]] to [[Declaration of a New Order|reorganize]] the Republic into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] with himself as its [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]].<ref name="EpisodeIII" /> Under the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]], the old Senate Guard was ultimately phased out.<ref name="EncyclopediaSG" /> Emperor Palpatine reorganized his red-robed bodyguards into the [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Emperor's Royal Guard]].<ref name="EpisodeIII" />

==Equipment==
{{Quote|Well trained the Supreme Chancellor's Red Guards are.|Grand Master Yoda|<ref name="LOE" />}}
Although the Red Guard originated from the ranks of the Senate Guard, they differed from their blue counterparts both aesthetically and in the design of their armor and equipment.<ref name="Bloodlines" /> Red Guards wore face-concealing helmets with a darkened visor,<ref name="EpisodeII" /> visually reminiscent<ref name="ISB">''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''</ref> to those worn by the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]]-[[Order of the Sith Lords|affiliated]]<ref name="Plagueis">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> [[Thyrsus/Legends|Thyrsus]] [[Sun Guard]],<ref name="ISB" /> in contrast to the Senate Guards' face-revealing helmets.<ref name="EpisodeI">{{Film|I}}</ref> Furthermore, they used a meter-long [[Force pike/Legends|force pike]] as a primary weapon while concealing their crimson [[Armor/Legends|armor]] beneath a voluminous red robe.<ref name="EpisodeII" /><ref name="EpisodeIII" /> Their force pikes were also considered lethal, in stark contrast to the stun rifles utilized by their blue counterparts.<ref name="Visual Dictionary" /><ref name="Complete Visual Dictionary" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Red_guard_conceptart.jpg|thumb|Red Guard concept art.]]
The Red Guard did not make its first appearance in the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series until the [[The Clone Wars: Season Five|fifth season]] episode "[[The Lawless]]."

